      "text": [
        " : «اَلْمُحْرِمُ يُمْسِكُ عَلَى أَنْفِهِ مِنَ اَلرِّيحِ اَلطَّيِّبَةِ وَ لاَ يُمْسِكُ عَلَى أَنْفِهِ مِنَ اَلرِّيحِ اَلْخَبِيثَةِ»."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.2670 - Al-Halabi and Muhammad ibn Muslim narrated from Abu Abdullah (as), who said:\n\"A Muhrim may cover his nose from a pleasant fragrance but should not cover his nose from an unpleasant odor.\""
